CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 10 reads: "A Bride And Her Gifts.....Just We Two.....Two Happy Lookeroners - Pretty Mrs. Edward English...the former Miss Anna Mae Powell...as she viewed her gifts at her marriage reception in her family residence in...Saturday evening. The couple, pictured center, were married Friday in parsonage of the Rev. Green.  They will live at 3443 Milwaukee street...Harris Photos
TitMainTitle: Anna Mae Powell English wearing floral dress and corsage, holding porcelain figure of woman, seated with gifts in family home for wedding reception
